abstract: >
  HERESY is a self-replicating build simulator written in Rust that writes, compiles,
  and runs C code that itself writes, compiles, and runs C code. A recursive act of
  defiance against sensible build systems, designed to offend purists and amuse the brave.
  Includes recursion guards, GitHub CI, and 100% existential dread.
